      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Michael Sherwin</b>\n</p><p><b>Michael J. Sherwin</b>,<br />\nan American computer chess programmer, and stockbroker <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>. \nHe is author of the <a href=\"/WinBoard\" title=\"WinBoard\">WinBoard</a> compatible chess engine <a href=\"/RomiChess\" title=\"RomiChess\">RomiChess</a>, which is famous for its <a href=\"/Learning\" title=\"Learning\">learning approach</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>. Michael's interests in <a href=\"/Bitboards\" title=\"Bitboards\">bitboards</a> and methods to generate <a href=\"/Sliding_Piece_Attacks\" title=\"Sliding Piece Attacks\">sliding piece attacks</a> did result in his index based approach, coined by <a href=\"/Harald_L%C3%BC%C3%9Fen\" title=\"Harald Lüßen\">Harald Lüßen</a> as <a href=\"/Sherwin_Bitboards\" title=\"Sherwin Bitboards\">Sherwin Bitboards</a>, and more recently <a href=\"/SISSY_Bitboards\" title=\"SISSY Bitboards\">SISSY Bitboards</a>, as applied in his new engine <a href=\"/index.php?title=Bricabrac&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Bricabrac (page does not exist)\">Bricabrac</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#2005_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2005 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n<li